From re- cords given by Lodge (ubi supra), and from others given by Lynch (Feudal Dignities, p. 290), it appears, that in the summer of 1204 De Courcy was at liberty, having given hos- tages to surrender himself when called upon; that he was so called upon after August 31 ; and it would seem that he did surrender him- self after October 21, 011 which day he had a safe conduct till the following Mid-Lent.
